Rationale: Figure 3: "Examples of localization of KIF1Bβ at postsynaptic sites (co-localization with polymerized F-actin, as revealed by phalloidin staining) are indicated with white arrows (blue and red color merges to purple), while examples of co-localization of KIF1B and synaptophysin (a presynaptic marker) are indicated with yellow arrows (green and red color merges to yellow)". Experimental description: M&M: "Spinal motor neurons and cortical neurons were obtained from E18-19 mice."

antibody;
"A rabbit polyclonal antibody to synthetic peptide IRSKLSRRCPSQSKY [aa residues 1,756-1,770 in human KIF1Bβ (NM015074)] was custom-made and affinity-purified by Peptide Speciality Laboratories, Germany. It was used at a dilution of 1:500 for immunoblotting and 1:300 for immunofluorescence (IF)."
